{"title_page": "List of films about 1971 India-Pakistan war", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe following films were made about 1971 Bangladesh-Pakistan war, through which [[Bangladesh]] got independence:\n\n==India==\n*''[[Border (1997 film)]]'', Hindi language film about [[Battle of Longewala]].<ref name=\"TOI_top10_films\">{{cite news|title=Top 10 films on Indo-Pak conflict|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/top-lists/top-10-films-on-indo-pak-conflict/videols/7824538.cms|accessdate=28 July 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=30 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511042921/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/top-lists/top-10-films-on-indo-pak-conflict/videols/7824538.cms|archive-date=11 May 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/border-director-jp-dutta-pays-tributes-paid-to-brig-chandpuri/articleshow/71557191.cms|title='Border' director JP Dutta pays tribute to Brig Chandpuri &#124; Chandigarh News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n*''[[Hindustan Ki Kasam]]'' (1973), Hindi film directed by [[Chetan Anand (director)|Chetan Anand]] on [[Operation Cactus Lilly]].<ref name=\"TOI_top10_films\"/>\n*''[[16 December (film)|16 December]]'', 2002 film directed by [[Mani Shankar]]\n*''[[1971 (2007 film)|1971]]'' (2007), Hindi film about Indian prisoners of war after the Indo-Pakistani War of 1971.<ref name=\"TOI_top10_films\"/>  \n*''[[1971: Beyond Borders]]'', 2017 [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam film]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/the-thrill-lies-in-being-the-first-person-to-do-something-that-has-not-been-done-before-mohanlal/articleshow/57839218.cms|title=The thrill lies in being the first person to do something that has not been done before: Mohanlal - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n*''[[Children of War (2014 film)]], drama film set during [[Bangladesh Liberation War]]\n*''[[The Ghazi Attack]], 2017 Hindi-Telugu bilingual film based on the mysterious sinking of [[PNS Ghazi]] during the War.\n*''[[Raazi]], 2017 [[Spy film]] set before the events of war.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/That-spy-princess/article15446864.ece|title=That spy princess!|date=2008-05-03|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-05-10|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n*''[[Romeo Akbar Walter]], 2017 spy film.\n\n==Bangladesh==\n*[[Guerrilla (2011 film)|Guerrilla]]\n*[[Matir Moyna]] (2002)\n*[[Hangor Nodi Grenade]] (1997)\n*[[Ora Egaro Jon]] (1972)\n*[[Abar Tora Manush Ho]] (1974)\n*[[Roktakto Bangla]] (1972)\n*[[Alor Michhil]]hi\n*[[Joyjatra]] (2004)\n*[[Aguner Poroshmoni]] (1994)\n*[[Shyamol Chaya]] (2004)\n*[[Desh Premik]] (1994)\n*[[Amar Bondhu Rashed]] (2011)\n*[[Shongram]] (2014)\n*[[Jibon Theke Neya]] (1970)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of war films]]\n[[Category:Lists of films by setting]]\n[[Category:Films based on the Bangladesh Liberation War]]\n[[Category:Indian war films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThe following films were made about 1971 Bangladesh-Pakistan war, through which [[Bangladesh]] got independence:\n\n==India==\n*''[[Border (1997 film)]]'', Hindi language film about [[Battle of Longewala]].<ref name=\"TOI_top10_films\">{{cite news|title=Top 10 films on Indo-Pak conflict|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/top-lists/top-10-films-on-indo-pak-conflict/videols/7824538.cms|accessdate=28 July 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=30 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120511042921/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/top-lists/top-10-films-on-indo-pak-conflict/videols/7824538.cms|archive-date=11 May 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/border-director-jp-dutta-pays-tributes-paid-to-br