ws/newsid=1352110/index.html|title=Golden awards for top FIFA World Cup Trio|website=www.fifa.com|date = 15 December 2010|accessdate = 8 February 2011}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|FIFA World Cup Dream Team]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup#Awards|2010]]\n*[[UEFA European Football Championship Teams of the Tournament|UEFA Euro Team of the Tournament]]: [[UEFA Euro 2008#Awards|2008]], [[UEFA Euro 2012#Awards|2012]]\n*[[UEFA Team of the Year]]: [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2007|2007]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2008|2008]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2009|2009]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2010|2010]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2011|2011]], [[UEFA Team of the Year#Team of the Year 2012|2012]]\n*[[European Sports Magazines#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]]: [[European Sports Magazines#2007\u201308|2008]]\n*[[UEFA Team of the Year#UEFA Ultimate Team of the Year|UEFA Ultimate Team of the Year]] (published 2019)<ref name=\"UUTOTY\">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2589565.html |title=Ultimate Team of the Year: the all-time XI |website=www.uefa.com|date=25 November 2019 |accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Golden Foot]]: 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2017/11/08/5a02d415ca47415c388b4610.html|title=Casillas admits retirement is looming following Golden Foot award|website=www.marca.com|date=8 November 2017|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Records===\n*[[European Cup and UEFA Champions League records and statistics#Appearances|Most appearances in the UEFA Champions League]]: 177 (excluding 4 appearances in the qualifying rounds)<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2018/12/13/football/1544694127_187030.html |title=Champions League: Iker Casillas still setting European records |website=en.as.com |date=13 December 2018 |accessdate=14 December 2018 }}</ref>\n*Most group stage appearances in the UEFA Champions League: 94<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2568008.html |title=Champions League group stage records and statistics |website=www.uefa.com |date= 12 December 2018 |accessdate=14 December 2018 }}</ref>\n*[[European Cup and UEFA Champions League records and statistics#Most wins|Second-most victories in the UEFA Champions League]]: 101 (behind [[Cristiano Ronaldo]])<ref name=\"100 wins UCL\">{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2018/12/11/football/1544562087_716210.html |title=Casillas reaches 100 Champions League wins |website=en.as.com |date=11 December 2018 |accessdate=14 December 2018 }}</ref>\n*[[European Cup and UEFA Champions League records and statistics#Goalkeeping|Most clean sheets in the UEFA Champions League]]: 57 (excluding 2 in the qualifying rounds)<ref name=\"Champions League's greatest ever goalkeepers\"/>\n*Most consecutive seasons in the UEFA Champions League: 20<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2564139.html |title=Record 20th Champions League campaign for Casillas |website=www.uefa.com |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=14 December 2018 }}</ref>\n*First player in Champions League history to reach the knock-out stages 19 times<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n*First goalkeeper to win 100 Champions League matches<ref>{{cite web |title=Casillas reaches 100 Champions League wins|url=https://en.as.com/en/2018/12/11/football/1544562087_716210.html |website=en.as.com |accessdate=14 December 2018 |date=11 December 2018}}</ref>\n*Youngest goalkeeper to play in a UEFA Champions League final: 19 years and four days<ref name=\"Iker Casillas ESPN Profile\"/><ref name=\"Champions League's greatest ever goalkeepers\"/>\n*Youngest goalkeeper to win a UEFA Champions League final: 19 years and four days<ref name=\"Iker Casillas ESPN Profile\"/><ref name=\"Champions League's greatest ever goalkeepers\"/>\n*[[European Cup and UEFA Champions League records and statistics#Penalties|Most penalty kicks saved in the UEFA Champions League]] (excluding shoot-outs): 7 out of 23<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2564018.html |title=All you ever wanted to know: Champions League penalties |website=www.uefa.com |date=6 December 2018 |accessdate=14 December 2018 }}</ref>\n*Most UEFA Champions League titles won by a goalkeeper: 3 (alongside [[Juan Alonso]], [[Ray Clemence]], [[Sepp Maier]], [[Keylor Navas]], [[Heinz Stuy]], [[V\u00edctor Vald\u00e9s]] and [[Kiko Casilla]])<ref name=\"Champions League's greatest ever goalkeepers\"/>\n*[[UEFA club competition records and statistics#Top appearances in UEFA club competitions|Most appearances in UEFA Club competitions]]: 188 (177 in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], 4 in the Champions League qualifying rounds, 2 in the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], 3 in the [[UEFA Super Cup]], 2 in the [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]])<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2503036.html |title=Who has made more than 150 UEFA club appearances |website=www.uefa.com|date=12 December 2018 |accessdate=14 December 2018 }}</ref>\n*Most appearances for Real Madrid in UEFA Club Competitions: 155<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/teams/club=50051/profile/index.html|title=Real Madrid CF|website=www.uefa.com|accessdate=20 March 2018}}</ref>\n*Most [[IFFHS World's Best Goalkeeper]] Awards: 5 (alongside Gianluigi Buffon)<ref name=\"Former Results\"/>\n*Most appearances by a goalkeeper in the [[FIFPro World XI]]: 5\n*Most appearances by a goalkeeper in the [[UEFA Team of the Year]]: 6<ref name=\"UUTOTY\"/>\n*Second-most appearances for the Spain national team: 167 (behind [[Sergio Ramos]])<ref name=\"Most-capped players\">{{cite web |url = http://eu-football.info/_players.php?id=185 |title = Statistics&nbsp;\u2013 Most-capped players |website=eu-football.info |accessdate =9 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Most caps\">{{cite web |url = http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/c/rankingPSEL.html |title = Ranking&nbsp;\u2013 Played Matches |website=www.bdfutbol.com |accessdate =28 December 2015}}</ref>\n*Most international clean sheets: 102<ref name=\"International feats\"/><ref name=\"100 clean sheets for Spain\"/>\n*Second-most international victories: 121<ref name=\"International feats\"/><ref name=\"Most caps\"/> (behind [[Sergio Ramos]])<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2019/06/07/5cfa4f1746163f39098b45a0.html|title=Sergio Ramos set to break world record|website=www.marca.com|date=7 June 2019}}</ref>\n*Fewest goals conceded by a FIFA World Cup-winning goalkeeper in a single edition of the tournament: 2 goals in 7 appearances (alongside Gianluigi Buffon and [[Fabien Barthez]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2006/4991652.stm|title=Italy 1\u20131 France (aet)|website=news.bbc.co.uk|author=Jonathan Stevenson|accessdate=8 December 2015}}</ref>\n*Most clean sheets in a single edition of the FIFA World Cup: 5 (alongside Gianluigi Buffon, [[Pascal Zuberb\u00fchler]], [[Oliver Kahn]], Fabien Barthez and [[Walter Zenga]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2090072-veteran-juventus-goalkeeper-gianluigi-buffon-still-vital-world-cup-cog-for-italy|title=Veteran Juventus Goalkeeper Gianluigi Buffon Still Vital World Cup Cog for Italy|website=bleacherreport.com|accessdate=30 October 2014}}</ref>\n*Most FIFA World Cup tournaments played in by a Spanish player: 4 (alongside Xavi, Andoni Zubizarreta and Fernando Hierro)\n*[[List of UEFA European Championship records#Goalkeeping|Longest unbeaten run at the UEFA European Championship]]: 509 minutes<ref name=\"Casillas, world record-breaking goalkeeper\"/>\n*Most clean sheets at the UEFA European Championship: 9 (alongside Edwin van der Sar)\n*Fewest goals conceded in a single edition of the UEFA European Championship: 1 (in 2012, alongside Gianluigi Buffon, [[Thomas Myhre]], and Dino Zoff)\n*[[List of UEFA European Championship records#Penalty shootouts|Most penalty kicks saved in penalty shoot-outs at the UEFA European Championship]]: 3 (alongside Gianluigi Buffon)\n\n===Decorations===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Decoration\n!Year Decorated\n|-\n|[[Royal Order of Sports Merit|Gold Medal of the Royal Order of Sporting Merit]]\n|2009<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.as.com/futbol/articulo/csd-concede-casillas-medalla-oro/dasftb/20091115dasdasftb_12/Tes | title = El CSD concede a Casillas la Medalla de Oro de la Real Orden del M\u00e9rito Deportivo | website=www.as.com | date = 15 November 2009 | accessdate =8 February 2011 | language = Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n|Favourite son of [[Navalacruz]]\n|2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/2010/08/30/futbol/equipos/real_madrid/1283169461.html?a=PROCT1ea85621d8b9a9620e22dd285d069ec3&t=1283179799|title=Casillas se emociona tras ser nombrado Hijo Predilecto de Navalacruz | website=www.marca.com | date = 30 August 2010 | accessdate =8 February 2011 | language = Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n|Favourite son of [[M\u00f3stoles]]\n|2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.as.com/futbol/articulo/iker-casillas-sera-nombrado-hijo/dasftb/20100830dasdasftb_18/Tes|title=Iker Casillas ser\u00e1 nombrado Hijo Predilecto de M\u00f3stoles el pr\u00f3ximo 16 de septiembre| website=www.as.com | date = 30 August 2010 | accessdate =8 February 2011 | language = Spanish}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Royal Order of Sports Merit|Royal Order of Sports Merit Cross]]\n|2015<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.marca.com/en/2015/11/10/en/football/spanish_football/1447161925.html|title = Casillas: \"I hope I'm remembered not only for my sporting achievements\"|date = 10 November 2015|accessdate = 10 November 2015|website=www.marca.com|last = |first = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.espnfc.com/spain/story/2707637/iker-casillas-top-spain-sport-honour-royal-order-grand-cross|title = Iker Casillas handed Spain's top sports honour with Royal Order Grand Cross|date = 10 November 2015|accessdate = 10 November 2015|website=www.espnfc.com}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of footballers with 100 or more caps]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.ikercasillas.es}}\n* {{FIFA}}\n* {{UEFA}}\n* {{NFT}}\n* [http://www.realmadrid.com/en/football/squad/iker-casillas-fernandez Profile] on [[Real Madrid]] official website\n* {{BDFutbol|1090}}\n* [http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/j1090.html?cat=SEL National team data] at BDFutbol\n* {{ForaDeJogo|198105200006|Iker Casillas}}\n* {{Soccerbase|19973}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Spain squads\n| bg        = #C60B1E\n| fg        = #FBEA0E\n| bordercolor = #000033\n|list1 =\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2000}}\n{{Spain squad 2002 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2004}}\n{{Spain squad 2006 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2008}}\n{{Spain squad 2009 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2012}}\n{{Spain squad 2013 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards\n|bg = gold\n|fg = navy\n|list1 =\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box|title=[[Princess of Asturias Awards#Sports (Deportes)|Prince of Asturias Award for Sports]]<br />(shared with [[Xavi]])|before=[[Haile Gebrselassie]]<br />{{flag|Ethiopia}}|after=[[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Olaz\u00e1bal]]<br />{{flag|Spain}}|years=2012}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Bravo award winners}}\n{{La Liga Zamora Trophy}}\n{{La Liga Goalkeeper of the Year}}\n{{2007 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2008 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2009 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2010 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2011 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2012 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{IFFHS World's Best Goalkeeper}}\n{{FIFA World Cup winning captains}}\n{{UEFA Euro Winning Captain}}\n{{UEFA Euro 2008 Team of the Tournament}}\n{{UEFA Euro 20