ous/casillas-intl.html|publisher=RSSSF|accessdate=27 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Iker Casillas|url=http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=3286|website=EU-Football.info|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref>\n[[File:President Zapatero with FIFA world cup (cropped).jpg|thumb|500px|Casillas and Prime Minister [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Rodr\u00edguez Zapatero]] holding the [[FIFA World Cup Trophy]] after Spain's victory in 2010]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|[[Spain national football team|Spain]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2000||6||0\n|-\n|2001||5||0\n|-\n|2002||11||0\n|-\n|2003||11||0\n|-\n|2004||12||0\n|-\n|2005||10||0\n|-\n|2006||10||0\n|-\n|2007||8||0\n|-\n|2008||15||0\n|-\n|2009||13||0\n|-\n|2010||15||0\n|-\n|2011||11||0\n|-\n|2012||16||0\n|-\n|2013||9||0\n|-\n|2014||8||0\n|-\n|2015||5||0\n|-\n|2016||2||0\n|-\n!Total!!167!!0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Real Madrid C'''\n*[[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[1998\u201399 Tercera Divisi\u00f3n|1998\u201399]] (Group VII)\n\n'''Real Madrid'''<ref name=\"RM honours\">[http://www.realmadrid.com/en/football/squad/iker-casillas-fernandez Honours]. Realmadrid.com. Retrieved on 26 September 2015.</ref><ref name=ikercasillasworld.com>[http://www.ikercasillasworld.com/en/ikercasillasoficial/sala-trofeos/ Iker Casillas | Trophies] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030112209/http://www.ikercasillasworld.com/en/ikercasillasoficial/sala-trofeos/ |date=30 October 2016 }}. Ikercasillasworld.com (15 September 1999). Retrieved on 26 September 2015.</ref>\n*[[La Liga]]: [[2000\u201301 La Liga|2000\u201301]], [[2002\u201303 La Liga|2002\u201303]], [[2006\u201307 La Liga|2006\u201307]], [[2007\u201308 La Liga|2007\u201308]], [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]]\n*[[Copa del Rey]]: [[2010\u201311 Copa del Rey|2010\u201311]], [[2013\u201314 Copa del Rey|2013\u201314]]\n*[[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]: [[2001 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2001]], [[2003 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2003]], 