{"title_page": "Anja Nobus", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n'''Anja Nobus''' (born 9 April 1974) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[cycling|cyclist]]. She participates in both road cycling as in [[cyclo-cross]]. In 2002 and 2004 she became Belgian national champion in cyclo-cross, while in 2003 she became Belgian road race champion.\n\n==Palmar\u00e8s==\n{{palmares start}}\n;2001\n:2nd [[Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships]]\n\n;2002\n:1st {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships]]\n\n;2003\n:1st {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Belgian National Road Race Championships]]\n:1st [[Gravere]]-[[Asper, Belgium|Asper]]\n:2nd [[Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships]]\n:1st [[Lille]], [[Belgium]]\n:3rd [[Hoogerheide]]\n:3rd [[Kalmthout]]\n\n;2004\n:1st {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships]]\n:3rd [[Oostmalle]]\n:2nd [[Gravere]]-[[Asper, Belgium|Asper]]\n\n;2005\n:2nd [[Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships]]\n:1st [[Lille]], [[Belgium]]\n:3rd [[Gravere]]-[[Asper, Belgium|Asper]]\n\n;2006\n:3rd [[Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships]]\n:2nd [[Lille]], [[Belgium]]\n:3rd [[Sint-Michielsgestel]] ([[2006/07 Cyclo-cross Superprestige]])\n{{palmares end}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Cycling archives|5681}}\n\n{{use dmy dates|date=November 2010}}\n{{Belgian National Road Race Championships (women)}}\n{{Belgian National Cyclo-cross Championships (women)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nobus, Anja}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Belgian female cyclists]]\n[[Category:Cyclo-cross cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Bruges]]\n[[Category:Belgian cyclo-cross champions]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Anja Nobus''' (born 9 April 1974) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[cycling|cyclist]]. She participates in both road cycling as in [[cyclo-cross]]. In 2002 and 2004 she became Belgian national champion in cyclo-cross, while in 2003 she became Belgian road race champion.\n\n==Palmar\