{"title_page": "Anja Lenaers", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Anja Lenaers\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Anja Lenaers\n| nickname       =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1972|3|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Membruggen]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| proteam1       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n| updated        =\n}}\n'''Anja Lenaers''' (born 28 March 1972) is a Belgian former [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. She finished in third place in the [[Belgian National Road Race Championships]] in 1994, 1997 and 1998.<ref name=\"CyclingArchives\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=29414 |title=Anja Lenaers |accessdate=4 May 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|29414}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lenaers, Anja}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian female cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Limburg (Belgium)]]\n[[Category:People from Riemst]]\n{{Belgium-cycling-bio-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Anja Lenaers\n| image          =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Anja Lenaers\n| nickname       =\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1972|3|28|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Membruggen]], [[Belgium]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| discipline     =\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| proyears1      =\n| proteam1       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n| updated        =\n}}\n